results.name: a(n) is the smallest k such that A336957(k) = n, or -1 if n does not appear in A336957.
comment: There is a strong conjecture that numbers n >= 3 appear in A336957 if and only if they are divisible by at least two different primes.
link: Scott R. Shannon, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
